unique_start_stations_name <- trpdata_aug_2022%>%
  filter(start_station_name != "") %>% 
  distinct(start_station_name)

unique_end_station_name <- trpdata_aug_2022%>%
  filter(end_station_name != "") %>% 
  distinct(end_station_name)

unique_stations <- 
  union(unique_end_station_name$end_station_name,
        unique_start_stations_name$start_station_name)

  • Finding the length of rides taken by riders by making a new column ride_length in minutes. And eliminating rides where start station and end station are same.
Code 
trpdata_aug_2022<- trpdata_aug_2022%>% 
  mutate(ride_length = difftime(ended_at, started_at,
                                units = "min")) %>%
  mutate(ride_length = as.numeric(ride_length)) %>% 
  mutate(ride_length = if_else(ride_length < 0, 0, ride_length)) %>% 
  filter(start_station_name != end_station_name) %>% 
  filter(ride_length >= 2)

  • Aggregating data to see âAverage minutes per rideâ grouped by âbike typeâ and ârider typeâ
Code 
trpdata_aug_2022_aggregate <- trpdata_aug_2022%>% 
  select(ride_id, rideable_type, member_casual, started_at, ended_at,
         ride_length, everything()) %>% 
  summarise(ride_count = n(), 
            ride_length = (sum(ride_length)),
            min_per_ride = ride_length/ride_count,
            .by = c(member_casual, rideable_type)) %>% gt()

  • Calculating and visualizing âAverage ride lengthâ by âRider typeâ.
Code 
average_ride_by_rideable_type <- trpdata_aug_2022%>% 
  summarise(ride_length = sum(ride_length),
            ride_id = n(),
            avg_ride_length = ride_length/ride_id,
            .by = c(rideable_type, member_casual)) %>%
  filter(rideable_type != "docked_bike") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(rideable_type, avg_ride_length)) + 
  geom_col(aes(fill = member_casual), position = "dodge")

average_ride_by_rideable_type

  • Calculating and visualising ride patterns in a week.
Code 
rideable_order <- c("classic_bike", "electric_bike", "docked_bike")

rides_on_days <- trpdata_aug_2022%>%
  filter(rideable_type != "docked_bike") %>% 
  mutate(rideable_type = factor(rideable_type, levels = rideable_order)) %>% ggplot(aes(wday(started_at, label = TRUE, abbr = FALSE))) + 
  geom_bar(aes(fill = member_casual), position = "dodge") +
  facet_wrap(~rideable_type) + labs(x = "Day of the Week", 
                                    y = "Number of rides") +
  theme(legend.position = "top",
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

  • Finding which route is traveled most by casual riders.
Code 
most_travelled_routes <- trpdata_aug_2022%>%
  filter(member_casual == "casual") %>% 
  summarise(ride_count = n(),
            avg_ride_length = mean(ride_length),
            minutes_per_ride = sum(ride_length)/ride_count,
            .by = c(stations_travelled)) %>%
  arrange(desc(ride_count))
